radiographic_examinations.findings: Fluid-filled blind-ending structure in the right lower quadrant measuring 11 mm in diameter with mucosal hyperenhancement and surrounding inflammatory fat stranding. No extraluminal air or drainable fluid collection identified. The bases of the lungs are clear, liver enhances homogeneously with no focal lesions, no intra or extrahepatic biliary ductal dilatation, and all other abdominal and pelvic organs appear normal.
